Walther chambered in 7.65MM/32ACP with 92-95% original hasty late war finish.  Walther Banner grips rate very good, showing some minor scratches and compression points. The German Police forces were quite different than the police forces here in the United States. The WWII German Police forces were composed of several para-military groups with duties ranging from standard police work to controlling the populations of the occupied territories. Some police forces fought the anti-Nazi Partisans and some even saw front line service. This pistol is a "Variation 4" PP Police. It features the somewhat crude unpolished military blue finish without slide legend and is simply manufacture code marked "ac" for Walther. It bears the Eagle/F Police acceptance stamp on the left side of the trigger guard. The Nazi Eagle test proofs appear on the slide, chamber and tip of barrel.
